=============================
       Linux, OS-X, BSD
=============================

Start by executing:
./bootstrap

To install add-ons into /path/to/Kodi:
./configure --prefix=/path/to/Kodi
make install

To build all content add-ons as .zip archives:
./configure
make zip

=============================
           Windows
=============================
Building the content addons standalone:
-----------------------------------
Prepare:
1) Install Visual Studio Express 2013 from http://www.visualstudio.com/en-us/downloads
   (follow the instructions on the wiki for Kodi itself)

Compile:
2) Run project\BuildDependencies\DownloadBuildDeps.bat
3) Open this solution from project\VS2010Express\XBMC Peripheral Addons.sln
4) Select the wanted configuration "Debug" or "Release"
5) Press F7 to build the solution

Install:
Still a TODO. The buildsystem does not yet generate .zip archives.

Workaround:
Run ConfigureAddonXML.bat, and then copy the wanted content addons to your Kodi
installation by hand.

Example:
addons\peripheral.joysticks\addon\*.* => YOUR_KODI_DIR\addons\peripheral.joysticks\*.*

